org.jsimpledb.kv

Class KVPairIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jsimpledb.kv.KVPairIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterator<KVPair>

    public class KVPairIterator
extends Object
implements Iterator<KVPair>
    An Iterator that iterates over all key/value pairs in a KVStore within a contiguous range of keys, without using the KVStore.getRange() method. Therefore, it can be used to implement KVStore.getRange() in KVStore implementaions that don't natively support iteration.

    The iteration is instead implemented using KVStore.getAtLeast(), KVStore.getAtMost(), and KVStore.remove(). Instances support repositioning, forward or reverse iteration, and removal.

      • setNextTarget

        public void setNextTarget(byte[] targetKey)
        Set the next target key.

        This is the key we will use to find the next element via KVStore.getAtLeast(byte[]) (or KVStore.getAtMost(byte[]) if this is a reverse iterator). Note that in the forward case, this is an inclusive lower bound on the next key, while in the reverse case it is an exclusive upper bound on the next key.

        Parameters:
        targetKey - next lower bound (exclusive) if going forward, or upper bound (exclusive) if going backward, or null to immediately end the iteration
